{"failure_class": "logic_error", "evidence": "The code attempts to calculate inversions using a nested loop and a helper function, but the logic for counting inversions is incorrect.", "replacement_block": "long long count_inversions(const vector<int>& nums) {
    int n = nums.size();
    vector<int> sorted_nums(nums);
    sort(sorted_nums.begin(), sorted_nums.end());

    vector<int> rank(n + 1, 0);
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        rank[lower_bound(sorted_nums.begin(), sorted_nums.end(), nums[i]) - sorted_nums.begin()] = i + 1;
    }

    vector<int> tree(2 * n, 0);
    long long inversions = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        inversions += i - rank[i] + 1;
        ++tree[n + rank[i]];
        for (int j = 2 * rank[i]; j > 0; j >>= 1) {
            --tree[j];
        }
    }
    return inversions;
}", "plan_was_wrong": false}

